ic%20landscape.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20ratings%20agency%20Moody's%20lowered%20the%20credit%20ratings%20of%2010%20small-%20and%20mid-sized%20US%20banks%20by%20one%20rung%2C%20and%20placed%20a%20slate%20of%20larger%20firms%20under%20review%20for%20potential%20downgrades%2C%20with%20Bank%20of%20New%20York%20Mellon%2C%20US%20Bancorp%2C%20Northern%20Trust%2C%20and%20State%20Street%20among%20the%20bigger%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20that%2C%20but%20Moody's%20reported%20a%20negative%20outlook%20for%2011%20financial%20firms%2C%20including%20Capital%20One%2C%20Citizens%20Financial%2C%20and%20Fifth%20Third%20Bancorp.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20what%20amounted%20to%2027%20rating%20actions%20on%20US%20banks%2C%20Moody's%20pointed%20to%20rising%20costs%20of%20capital%2C%20deteriorating%20profits%2C%20and%20climbing%20risks%20to%20assets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBank%20stocks%20retreated%20Tuesday%2C%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Finvesco-kbw-bank-etf-us46138e6288%5C%22%3EKBW%20Nasdaq%20Bank%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%20down%20almost%202%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBehind%20the%20action%20is%20what%20Moody's%20says%20is%20a%20more%20difficult%20operating%20environment%20for%20banks%20amid%20higher%20interest%20rates%2C%20an%20uncertain%20base%20of%20deposits%2C%20and%20a%20murky%20outlook%20for%20the%20broader%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20date%2C%20stress%20on%20US%20banks%20has%20been%20reflected%20almost%20exclusively%20in%20funding%20and%20interest%20rate%20risk%20related%20to%20monetary%20policy%20tightening%2C%20but%20a%20worsening%20in%20asset%20quality%20will%20likely%20come%2C%26quot%3B%20Moody's%20wrote%20in%20a%20Monday%20report.%20%26quot%3BWe%20continue%20to%20expect%20a%20mild%20recession%20in%20early%202024%2C%20and%20given%20the%20funding%20strains%20on%20the%20US%20banking%20sector%2C%20there%20will%20likely%20be%20a%20tightening%20of%20credit%20conditions%20and%20rising%20loan%20losses%20for%20US%20banks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20effect%2C%20much%20of%20the%20stress%20on%20banks%20Moody's%20is%20responding%20to%20can%20be%20chalked%20up%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20policy%20decisions%20over%20the%20past%20year%20and%20a%20half.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20downgrades%20follow%2011%20interest%20rate%20hikes%20from%20the%20Fed%20since%20March%202022%2C%20and%20just%20five%20months%20since%20the%20last%20bank%20crisis%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fsilicon-valley-bank-collapse-sivb-wall-street-reaction-financial-crisis-2023-3%5C%22%3Estarted%20with%20Silicon%20Valley%20Bank%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20ended%20up%20dragging%20down%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Ffirst-republic-stock-bank-crisis-svb-wall-street-rescue-2023-3%5C%22%3EFirst%20Republic%20Bank%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Signature%20Bank.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20just%20banks%20that%20are%20feeling%20pain.%20The%20rapidly%20tightening%20credit%20environment%20has%20hamstrung%20plenty%20of%20non-bank%20businesses%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fcorporate-debt-defaults-recession-credit-crunch-financial-crisis-default-rate-2023-7%5C%22%3Ecorporate%20debt%20defaults%20skyrocketing%20past%20last%20year's%20total%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EMoody's%20view%20of%20the%20banking%20landscape%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20the%20second%20quarter%2C%20Moody's%20found%20banks%20tightened%20underwriting%20standards%20for%20commercial%20and%20consumer%20loans%20and%20credit%20cards%2C%20which%20made%20business%20more%20difficult%20as%20funding%20costs%20climbed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuantitative%20tightening%2C%20the%20ratings%20firm%20said%2C%20has%20led%20to%20a%20general%20drain%20on%20deposit%20funding.%20Even%20though%20that%20moderated%20over%20the%20last%20three%20months%2C%20systemic%20risks%20remain%20that%20could%20hamper%20deposits%20in%20coming%20quarters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20banks'%20deposits%20were%20flat%20or%20down%20only%20modestly%2C%20but%20the%20mix%20worsened%2C%20with%20non-interest-bearing%20deposits%20declining%20and%20banks%20paying%20more%20for%20deposits%2C%26quot%3B%20Moody's%20strategists%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20resulting%20drop%20in%20net%20interest%20income%20and%20net%20interest%20margins%20eroded%20profitability%20and%2C%20thus%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20replenish%20capital%20internally.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20noted%20that%20many%20smaller%20banks%2C%20like%20the%20ones%20they%20downgraded%2C%20hold%20comparatively%20low%20regulatory%20capital%20compared%20to%20banking%20giants%20and%20global%20peers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high-rate%20landscape%2C%20then%2C%20puts%20some%20firms%20with%20%26quot%3Bsizable%20unrealized%20economic%20losses%26quot%3B%20that%20could%20eventually%20lead%20to%20a%20loss%20in%20investor%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20small%20and%20mid-size%20banks%20with%20exposure%20to%20commercial%20real%20estate%20have%20seen%20the%20quality%20of%20their%20assets%20deteriorate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BElevated%20CRE%20exposures%2C%26quot%3B%20Moody's%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bare%20a%20key%20risk%20given%20sustained%20high%20interest%20rates%2C%20structural%20declines%20in%20office%20demand%20due%20to%20remote%20work%2C%20and%20a%20reduction%20in%20the%20availability%20of%20CRE%20credit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221798%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Moody's%20bank%20lending%20standards%202023%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d2857611d6ad0019ed3f12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22867%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20Reserve%2C%20BLS%2C%20Moody's%20Investors%20Service%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3EIt's%20not%20just%20the%20Fed%20causing%20stress%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20report%20on%20Monday%2C%20Moody's%20also%20highlighted%20implications%20for%20banks%20of%20factors%20that%20aren't%20a%20direct%20result%20of%20Fed%20moves%2C%20including%20last%20year's%20UK%20gilt%20market%20chaos%20that%20pushed%20long-dated%20US%20Treasurys%20higher%20and%20weighed%20on%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20recession%20still%20in%20the%20cards%2C%20the%20macroeconomic%20outlook%20in%20general%20puts%20pressure%20on%20the%20US%20banking%20sector.%20Funding%20and%20profitability%20remain%20more%20difficult%20than%20years%20past%2C%20and%20their%20large%20holdings%20of%20fixed-rate%20assets%20isn't%20ideal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOther%20non-Fed%20factors%20such%20as%20heavy%20Treasury%20bond%20issuance%20and%20spillovers%20from%20monetary%20policy%20developments%20in%20Japan%20are%20also%20pushing%20US%20interest%20rates%20higher%2C%26quot%3B%20Moody's%20strategists%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%2010-year%20Treasury%20yield%20has%20risen%20both%20Q3%20to%20date%20and%20sequentially%20in%20Q2%20from%20Q1%2C%20even%20as%20the%20yield%20curve%20remains%20inverted%2C%20deepening%20some%20banks'%20ALM%20risk%20and%20profitability%20pressures.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20a%20downgrade%20of%20a%20company's%20credit%20rating%20makes%20borrowing%20more%20expensive.%20For%20most%20businesses%20this%20is%20a%20bad%20thing%2C%20but%20banks%20aren't%20like%20most%20businesses.%20For%20one%2C%20they've%20got%20a%20large%20pool%20of%20low-cost%20capital%20in%20the%20form%20of%20deposits.%20Even%20as%20they%20pay%20more%20interest%20on%20deposits%20this%20year%2C%20it's%20still%20cheap%20compared%20to%20borrowing%20in%20the%20bond%20market.%20So%20Moody's%20downgrades%20aren't%20all%20doom%20and%20gloom%20for%20these%20firms%2C%20and%20it's%20always%20possible%20the%20moves%20are%20reversed%20once%20the%20outlook%20turns%20rosier.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Bell%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20law%20firm%20Honigman%20and%20co-chair%20of%20th